This paper presents a transfer learning mechanism for sequential data using pre-trained black box models, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also applies this technique to personalized language modeling, which is a subfield of natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper involves the use of recurrent neural networks, which is a popular technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the consistency of estimation, which is a topic in cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper uses a hidden Markov model, which is a common tool in statistical modeling and machine learning (cs.SD).
